# DatalakeAttendance — Cursor Operational Rules
# NHAI Hackathon 7.0 | Offline Face Auth | React Native 0.85

## Project Context
Offline-first mobile attendance system for NHAI field personnel. Fully offline
facial recognition + liveness detection. Targets Android 8.0+ / iOS 12+.
Total AI model footprint must stay ≤ 20 MB.

## Technology Stack
- Framework : React Native 0.85 (TypeScript)
- Camera     : react-native-vision-camera v4 + JSI Frame Processors
- AI Models  : MediaPipe Face Mesh TFLite (~3.2 MB) + MobileFaceNet INT8 (2.02 MB ✓ exported)
- Storage    : react-native-mmkv (AES-256 encrypted)
- Navigation : @react-navigation/bottom-tabs
- Network    : @react-native-community/netinfo
- Location   : react-native-geolocation-service

## Directory Layout (DO NOT change without reason)
src/
  components/   — Shared UI (CameraOverlay reticle etc.)
  db/           — mmkv.ts: SINGLE source for all encrypted storage & interfaces
  native/       — FaceProcessor.ts: JS bridge to native frame processor plugin
  screens/      — RegisterScreen, CheckInScreen, AdminSyncScreen
  utils/        — faceMath.ts (EAR/MAR/cosine), locationManager.ts
  App.tsx       — Tab navigator root
App.tsx         — SafeAreaProvider wrapper + StatusBar

## Coding Rules
1. All storage reads/writes MUST go through src/db/mmkv.ts.
2. Never store face vectors in plain text; always use the encrypted MMKV instance.
3. Frame Processors run on the native thread — keep JS callbacks minimal.
4. All async operations must be wrapped in try/catch.
5. Use TypeScript strict mode; no `any` types unless absolutely unavoidable.
6. Keep every file under 300 lines; split if larger.
7. Do not add third-party packages that require paid licenses.
8. Model files (.tflite) live in android/app/src/main/assets/ and ios/DatalakeAttendance/.
9. UI colour palette: bg #0f172a, surface #1e293b, accent #3b82f6, text #f8fafc.
10. All liveness thresholds (EAR < 0.25 for blink, MAR > 0.6 for smile) are defined
    only in src/utils/faceMath.ts — do not hardcode elsewhere.

## Phase Checklist
- [x] Phase 1 — Project setup, MMKV DB, screens, navigation
- [x] Phase 2 — Vision Camera + Frame Processor plugin skeleton
- [ ] Phase 3 — MediaPipe TFLite integration → landmark output
- [ ] Phase 4 — MobileFaceNet enrollment → store vector in MMKV
- [ ] Phase 5 — Liveness (EAR/MAR) + cosine similarity check-in
- [x] Phase 6 — Offline geolocation with 4s timeout / 60s cache
- [x] Phase 7 — AdminSyncScreen: NetInfo → POST → purge on 200 OK
